NOTE : We usually don't give much importance to audio compared to video.But,for older classic comedy movies,dialogues and its throwing become more important than video sometimes. Frankly speaking,I couldn't continue watching this movie (with the DVD audio) after 10-15 minutes. Randomly varying noise intensity suppressed voice of the characters.It was really painful to ears to listen and understand the dialogues carried by strong noise.
Luckily,I got Mike Khan unengaged,he cleaned the raw DVD audio to the best possible level within few hrs on that day. Without MK's support, this rip wouldn't be complete.

As the brighter scenes were almost burnt in the DVD, I have to minimize static contrast level a bit without affecting shaded/dark regions,thus it looks more soothing to our eyes. Like all poor quality black and white movies, I cleaned it without loosing any details.
